On Fri, 6 Aug 1999, Martin Mares wrote:
> 
>    Is there any reason for devices knowing that about regions?
Yes. Mixed mode drivers: drivers that do both PCI and ISA devices, for
example.
>    I think that allocation of whole PCI devices (see pci_request_device()
> in my PCI patch posted on yesterday evening) should be enough.
It's not enough, and it's too much.
Sometimes you can validly have two drivers for two different parts of the
same PCI device. That device =may= show up as two different functions, but
that's not guaranteed. Think of PCI super-IO devices, for example.
		Linus
